article.headline: Florida Gulf Coast 87, Gardner-Webb 80
article.story: BOILING SPRINGS, N.C. (AP) -- Delvin Franklin scored 25 points, Casey Wohlleb added 20 and Florida Gulf Coast beat Gardner-Webb 87-80 on Saturday night. Terike Barrows had 15 points and Landon Adler finished with 12 for the Eagles (8-13, 4-3 Atlantic Sun), who shot 51 percent in completing a successful two-game trip to North Carolina. They won at Campbell two nights earlier. Nate Blank scored 25 points to lead Gardner-Webb (9-12, 3-4), which shot 42 percent and made 10 3-pointers but was outrebounded 44-40. Thomas Sanders added 18 points before fouling out and Grayson Flittner finished with 15 points on 4-of-14 shooting -- 4-of-12 from 3-point range -- for the Runnin' Bulldogs.
